This paper is primarily focused on the development and testing of an autonomous control system for a robotic limb with elastic elements. The paper discusses the challenges of modeling and controlling such a system, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores the impact of elasticity on learning and performance, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for autonomous control, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for learning and control, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
